<subSubSection id="D0BD7F7774484C1CAD6801C939ADA4B8" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" type="original description">
<paragraph id="C003F63604DFDFA990FC0C43273569C6" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Original description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="792CC15BDB92498958094E22FEF33727" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">
&quot; 
<emphasis id="DB0A82E184ADA80AFB78A210016DEA41" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">testula styliformis a ventre linearis, lateribus rectis, apicibus arcte constrictis late rotundatis</emphasis>
.&quot;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1DF937C7F7C88155B6279D4F6F23E856" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">
<bibRefCitation id="7BF0977007F6AD8F292E508A1975612F" author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Bibliotheca Diatomolgica" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 353" refId="B18" refString="Krammer, K, 1992. Pinnularia, eine Monographie der europaeischen Taxa. Bibliotheca Diatomolgica 26: 1 - 353" title="Pinnularia, eine Monographie der europaeischen Taxa." volume="26" year="1992">Krammer (1992</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 32, fig. 10) [reproduction of 
<normalizedToken id="AC757645417296A9A6FE7E11770E11B3" originalValue="Ehrenberg’s">Ehrenberg's</normalizedToken>
published figure (1843, Tafel I, Fig. IV:1)] defined an 
<normalizedToken id="AC77D1BD3E758B9ADFAD09DE11859AB9" originalValue="“iconotype”">&quot;iconotype&quot;</normalizedToken>
for 
<taxonomicName id="ADC5B09C982BC5E45C9A21E82D9CB129" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="" order="Naviculales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="microstauron">
<emphasis id="A7B9CBC83267F1B76389003D840A0D37" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Pinnularia microstauron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Since we found the specimen used by Ehrenberg to describe the species, we designated it here as lectotype of the species. 
<taxonomicName id="7C5C813C8CA0D2E8DCCD7CFFB3CF1FFE" authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1843" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Stauroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="" order="Naviculales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="microstauron">
<emphasis id="F53F5015062FBAAE116FA65FD149FEE3" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Stauroptera microstauron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described for two samples from Brazil and Canada (Labrador) (
<bibRefCitation id="171C64E64D47F005D25846985A5B543E" author="Ehrenberg, CG" journalOrPublisher="Bericht der Koeniglichen Akademie der Wissenschaften zu Berlin" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" refId="B7" refString="Ehrenberg, CG, 1843. Verbreitung und Einfluss des mikroskopischen Lebens in Sued- und Nord-Amerika. Abhandlungen der Koeniglichen Akademie der Wissenschaften in Berlin, Physk. Kl.1841: 291-445." title="Verbreitung und Einfluss des mikroskopischen Lebens in Sued- und Nord-Amerika. Abhandlungen der Koeniglichen Akademie der Wissenschaften in Berlin, Physk. Kl. 1841: 291 - 445." year="1843">Ehrenberg 1843</bibRefCitation>
, p. 387). However, we did not find any mentioning of 
<taxonomicName id="A5A03DF7977B3AB4248AD9A04F140C30" authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1843" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Stauroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="" order="Naviculales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="microstauron">
<emphasis id="6BE2FC92D69920B8DD7062475AB79301" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Stauroptera microstauron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the legends of the mica from Labrador (250509 to 250516). Therefore, we defined the lectotype from the material from Brazil.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
